    "Commentary Vol. 83": "And they journeyed, etc.] Jacob `[char_Jacob_Ref]` and his family, with all that were with them, from Shechem to Bethel: and the terror of God was upon the cities that [were] round about them; an exceeding great panic seized the inhabitants of the cities of the land of Canaan, all about Shechem, which was from God himself impressing it on their minds, through what the sons of Jacob `[char_Jacob_Ref]` had done to that city: and they did not pursue after the sons of Jacob `[char_Jacob_Ref]`; as it might have been thought they would, and take revenge on them for their ill usage of the inhabitants of a neighbouring city; but instead of this, they were afraid they should be used in the same manner; wherefore Jacob `[char_Jacob_Ref]` and his family journeyed in safety, and came to Bethel in peace.\nVer."
